str2: Adverb from the base of pou; an interrogative particle of manner; in what way?; also as exclamation, how much!

str2: From nous; to exercise the mind, i.e. to comprehend, heed.
Neuter of hostis as conjunction; demonstrative, that; causative, because.

str2: Answer, bid, bring word, command. A primary verb; to speak or say.
From the base of peran; properly, through, i.e. Around; figuratively with respect to; used in various applications, of place, cause or time.
Bread, a loaf, food. From airo; bread or a loaf.

str2: From pros and echo; to hold the mind towards, i.e. Pay attention to, be cautious about, apply oneself to, adhere to.
From, away from. A primary particle; 'off, ' i.e. Away, in various senses.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
Leaven, ferment, both lit. and met. Probably from zeo; ferment.
